The paper discusses a novel training approach for deep neural networks using low bit-width fixed-point data. This technique is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and robotics (cs.AR). However, given the focus on training deep neural networks, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.AR.
